<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
This genus is clearly distinguished from the other genera of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Wroughtonilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Wroughtonilla" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Wroughtonilla</taxonomicName>
group by the combination of the following character states: eyes extremely large; pronotum without superior marginal line of the pronotal hypomeron; pronotal disc quite convex, with a shallow and large longitudinal depression; pronotum and elytra covered with long, suberect macrosetae; and abdomen large, expanded, much wider than elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Peninsular Malaysia.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Only the type species 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Togpelenys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Togpelenys gigantea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">Togpelenys gigantea</taxonomicName>
Kistner, 1989 has been known in the genus. Probably further species will be found from the regions around Peninsular Malaysia, e.g., Sumatra, Borneo and Java.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
